<i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":0,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705190,"age":31,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Speeton was born in 1259, in England. She had at least 1 son with Aaron John FitzRoger. She died in 1313, in her hometown, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1259–1313":"1259–1313","1261–1301":"1261–1301","1280–1365":"1280–1365","1259":"1259","1313":"1313","1301":"1301","1365":"1365","1261":"1261","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","England":"England","Sawcock, England":"England"},"fi":{"1259–1313":"1259–1313","1261–1301":"1261–1301","1280–1365":"1280–1365","1259":"1259","1313":"1313","1301":"1301","1365":"1365","1261":"1261","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","England":"England","Sawcock, England":"England"},"fr":{"1259–1313":"1259–1313","1261–1301":"1261–1301","1280–1365":"1280–1365","1259":"1259","1313":"1313","1301":"1301","1365":"1365","1261":"1261","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","Sawcock, England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Margaret Speeton est née en 1259, à Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Aaron John FitzRoger. Elle est décédée en 1313, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 54 ans."},"de":{"1259–1313":"1259–1313","1261–1301":"1261–1301","1280–1365":"1280–1365","1259":"1259","1313":"1313","1301":"1301","1365":"1365",